### 8. Short-Form & Long-Form Content Skill Systems

## A. Short-Form Video Engine (15s – 60s)

### Core Objective

Instant hook → maximum retention → loop replay

### Structure

* 0–2s: **Shock Hook** (pattern interrupt)
* 2–10s: Context explosion (what is happening)
* 10–40s: Escalation (rapid visual changes)
* Last 3s: **Loop Ending / Open Question**

### Rules

* No slow intro
* Every 2–3 seconds must change visual/emotion
* End must connect to beginning (infinite loop feel)

### Style Signature

* Fast cuts
* Aggressive narration
* Minimal explanation
* High curiosity density

---

## B. Long-Form Video Engine (20–30 minutes)

### Core Objective

Deep immersion storytelling → emotional attachment → binge watching

### Structure (3-Act System + Retention Beats)

#### ACT 1 (0–5 min): Hook + World Setup

* Immediate crisis or mystery
* Introduce emotional stakes

#### ACT 2 (5–20 min): Escalation Spiral

* Problem expands
* New layers revealed every 1–2 minutes
* Sub-conflicts introduced

#### ACT 3 (20–30 min): Climax + Open Loop

* Peak conflict
* Partial resolution
* Final unresolved question (Part 2 trigger)

### Retention Mechanism

* Every 30–60 seconds: mini-hook injection
* Every 2–3 minutes: narrative twist
* Emotional reset points (fear → hope → fear)

